<h2>Emperor's Hammer Groups</h2>
<hr />
<h3>The Fringe</h3>
<p>The Fringe is the Subgroup of the Emperor's Hammer that focuses on the <a href="http://www.starwarsgalaxies.com" title="Click link for more information" target="_blank"><strong>Star Wars Galaxies</strong></a> MMORPG (Massive Multiplayer Online Role-Playing Game is a genre of computer role-playing games in which a very large number of players interact with one another within a virtual game world.) The &quot;adventures&quot; take place online in the always running MMORPG where you create and personalize your own character/avatar in both appearance, style and profession.</p>
Primary platforms:
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.starwarsgalaxies.com" title="Click link for more information" target="_blank"><strong>Star Wars Galaxies</strong></a></li>
</ul>
			
<p align="center"><a href="http://emperorshammer.org/subgroups/the_fringe/fringe.htm" target="blank"><img src="../images/fringebanner1.jpg" border="0" width="350" alt="Visit the Fringe" title="Visit the Fringe" /><br/>
Visit the Fringe of the Emperor's Hammer</a></p>

<hr />
<h3>Dark Brotherhood</h3>
<p>The Dark Brotherhood is an elite group of Force users within the Emperor's Hammer who focus on the aspects of the Dark Side. Under the direction of the Grand Master, the Brotherhood seeks out power in all of its forms. The members of the Sith Order seek power over others. The Obelisk Order seeks mastery of the battlefield to crush its enemies, and the Krath seek victory through knowledge.</p>
            
<p>Members of the Dark Brotherhood learn the arts of lightsaber combat and explore the power of the Dark Side. From the moment an initiate enters the Shadow Academy, the Dark Brotherhood's academic institution, they are trained in the ways of the Force but very few will posess the fortitude to persevere to attain the rank of Dark Jed Knight and earn the right to construct their own lightsabers.</p> 
Primary platforms and activities:
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.swtor.com" title="Click link for more information" target="_blank"><strong>Star Wars: The Old Republic</strong></a></li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star_Wars:_Dark_Forces" title="Click link for more information" target="_blank"><strong>Star Wars: Jedi Knight (Series)</strong></a></li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star_Wars:_Dark_Forces" title="Click link for more information" target="_blank"><strong>Star Wars: Dark Forces</strong></a></li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star_Wars_Jedi_Knight:_Dark_Forces_II" title="Click link for more information" target="_blank"><strong>Star Wars Jedi Knight: Dark Forces II</strong></a></li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star_Wars_Jedi_Knight_II:_Jedi_Outcast" title="Click link for more information" target="_blank"><strong>Star Wars Jedi Knight II: Jedi Outcast</strong></a></li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star_Wars_Jedi_Knight:_Jedi_Academy" title="Click link for more information" target="_blank"><strong>Star Wars Jedi Knight: Jedi Academy</strong></a></li>
</ul>

<p>Sith pilots of the Dark Brotherhood utilize the same flight sims as the pilots of the TIE Corps.<br />
Creative activities such as fiction writing, graphics creation, Star Wars RPG and many others are also available for participation.</p>			

